This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category as it deals with the task of video super-resolution, which is a common problem in computer vision. The use of perceptual loss functions and adversarial networks also suggests a focus on image processing and computer vision. 

Multimedia (cs.MM) is another likely category as the paper deals with video processing, which is a key component of multimedia applications. 

Machine Learning (cs.LG) is also a possible category as the paper proposes a novel adversarial recurrent network architecture, which is a type of machine learning model. 

Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new approach to video super-resolution that leverages deep learning techniques, which are a key component of AI research. 

Finally, Graphics (cs.GR) is a possible category as the paper deals with generating high-quality images and videos, which is a common problem in computer graphics.
